div1.p:
3.---A board of survey, to consist of:-

Major J. R. Kean, Surgeon, U. S. Volunteers;

Captain Edwin P. Brewer, 7th U.S. Cavalry;

1st Lieut. A. E. Truby, Assistant Surgeon, U.S. Army;

will convene at the Hospital Columbia Barracks for the purpose of

investigating, reporting upon, and fixing the responsibility for

the damage to and loss of certain medical and quartermaster's

supplies pertaining to Military Hospital No. 2, Havana, for which

Major S. P. Kramer, Surgeon, U. S. Volunteers, reports that he is

responsible.
